<1ST_LINE>u i PM-Dollar-Gold     03-07 0317</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Dollar-Gold,0337</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar Lower, Gold Prices Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar was lower in thin early European
trading today and foreign currency dealers said they don't expect
it to break out of a narrow trading range before new American trade
figures are released next week.
   Gold prices were mixed.
   The January trade report is due to be released March 17 and one
dealer at a U.S. bank in Frankfurt, West Germany, said the market
will be paralyzed until then.
   ``We just move along from trade figure to trade figure,'' he
said.
   In Tokyo, where trading ends as Europe's business day begins,
the dollar fell 0.35 yen to a closing 128.87. Later, in London, it
was quoted at 128.60 yen.
   Other dollar rates at midmorning, compared with late Friday:
   _1.6865 West German marks, down from 1.6940
   _1.3960 Swiss francs, down from 1.4030
   _5.7090 French francs, down from 5.7300
   _1.8952 Dutch guilders, down from 1.9010
   _1,243.75 Italian lire, down from 1,248.00
   _1.2535 Canadian dollars, down from 1.2547
   In London, one British pound cost $1.7972, more expensive than
late Friday's $1.7740.
   Traders said the pound was strong throughout Europe because of
relatively high British interest rates.
   Gold prices were lower in London and higher in Zurich.
   The metal opened in London at a bid price of $437 a troy ounce,
compared with late Friday's $437.50. At midmorning today, the
city's five major bullion dealers fixed a recommended price of $436.
   One bullion dealer said market participants in London were
taking profits following Friday's technical rally in New York.
   ``It is going to keep falling,'' he said. ``There is a lot of
selling around.''
   In Zurich, the bid price was $434.25, up from $432 late Friday.
   Earlier, in Hong Kong, gold rose 54 cents to close at a bid
$438.75.
   Silver was quoted in London today at a bid price of $6.38 a troy
ounce, down from Friday's $6.41.
</TEXT>
