<HEAD>Atlanta Councilman Charged After Carrying Weapon Into Airport</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   City Councilman Hosea Williams was charged with
carrying a weapon without a license when security officers at
Hartsfield Atlanta International Airport found a gun in his
briefcase at an airport checkpoint.
   The .38-caliber revolver was confiscated when Williams was
charged about 11:30 a.m. Sunday, but the councilman and civil
