<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Dishwasher Death,0170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sheriff's Department Says Death Of Boy In Dishwasher Was
Accidental</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The death of a 12-year-old boy whose nude
body was found in his family's portable dishwasher has been ruled
accidental, authorities said Monday.
   Brown County Coroner Genie Williams has not officially ruled on
a cause of death, but Cmdr. David Zasada said initial indications
are that Michael Conard ``very probably died of a lack of oxygen
prior to the hot water'' beginning to circulate in the machine a
week ago.
   The boy, who was 4-foot-10 and weighed about 90 pounds,
apparently used the soap dispenser inside the door to pull the door
shut, Zasada said. There is no release mechanism inside the
machine, he said.
   The boy took off his clothes and watch before climbing in
machine, apparently to see how it worked, Zasada said.
   Suicide was ruled out because there was no note and friends,
family and teachers indicated the boy was well-adjusted and happy,
Zasada said.
</TEXT>
