family values. Electronic Data Systems Corp., which he founded in
1962 with $1,000 of his own money, grew into a multibillion-dollar
company and was acquired by General Motors Corp. in 1984.
   The AP meeting is held on the first day of the American
Newspaper Publishers Association annual convention, scheduled this
year for April 25-27 in Honolulu.
