<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--Verity-USSR     03-07 0171</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Verity-USSR,160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Commerce Secretary To Lead US Delegation To Moscow Conference</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Commerce Secretary William Verity will lead a
U.S. delegation to the Soviet Union in April for a conference on
trade and economic cooperation, the Commerce Department said Monday.
   The meeting, of the Joint U.S.-U.S.S.R Commercial Commission, is
being held as a follow-up to the December summit meeting between
President Reagan and Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev.
   The two leaders, in a joint statement at the end of the summit
in Washington, instructed the commission to develop proposals to
expand the two nations' trade and economic ties.
   It will be the 10th meeting of the commission, which last met
December 1986 in Washington.
   While in Moscow, during the week of April 11, Verity will meet
with Gorbachev and address the U.S.-U.S.S.R. Trade and Economic
Council, an organization of U.S. companies and Soviet firms.
   Verity will be accompanied by representatives of the
Agriculture, Treasury and State departments, the National Security
Council and the office of the U.S. Trade Representative.
</TEXT>
