<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--MercyKilling     03-07 0143</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Mercy Killing,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Farmer Pleads Innocent To Murder In Wife's Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 77-year-old farmer on Monday pleaded
innocent by reason of mental deficiency to charges he fatally shot
his ailing wife.
   Oscar Carlson entered pleas of innocent and innocent by reason
of mental deficiency to charges of first- and second-degree murder
in Douglas County District Court.
   Carlson is charged with the shooting death last week of his wife
of 47 years. He reportedly told authorities he shot the 71-year-old
woman to end her suffering from Alzheimer's disease.
   Michael Dolan, an attorney for Carlson, said he asked the court
to reduce Carlson's $100,000 bail, and allow the man to post his
home and five acres as assurance against flight. Douglas County
Judge Donald Gray took the matter under advisement.
   Meanwhile, Carlson remained at the Douglas County Jail, Dolan
said.
</TEXT>
