<HEAD>Memorial To Composer Planned</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The American Society of Composers, Authors and
Publishers announced Monday that it will produce a memorial tribute
to composer Frederick Loewe in a Broadway theater on March 28.
   Confirmed to perform and-or speak are Julie Andrews, Richard
Harris, Louis Jordan, Robert Goulet, Agnes de Mille, Kitty Carlisle
Hart and Herman Levin, who produced Loewe's most famous musical,
``My Fair Lady.''
   Ken Sunshine of ASCAP said the theater will be announced later.
The tribute will be free and open to the public.
   Loewe and lyricist Alan Jay Lerner also wrote the songs for
``Brigadoon,'' ``Paint Your Wagon,'' ``Camelot'' and the movie
``Gigi.'' Loewe died Feb. 15; he was 86.
