<TEXT>
   The former chairman of a Connecticut
bank and a stockbroker have been charged in connection with insider
trading that allegedly occurred before the bank's 1986 purchase of
a bank in Maine.
   The indictments of Robert DiGennaro, 40, former chairman of the
Suffield Savings Bank, and Arthur Silverman, 62, of West Hartford
represented the first criminal insider trading charges brought in
Connecticut, U.S. Attorney Stanley Twardy said Friday.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices declined slightly Friday as the Dow Jones average
of 30 industrials slipped 5.63 to 2,057.86.
