<2ND_LINE>BC-South Korea-Auto,0188</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Auto Exports Nearly Double In February</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   South Korea's three automakers
reported Monday their combined exports soared 97.4 percent in
February, to 49,879 cars from 25,270 the same month last year.
   Officials said the February shipments were mostly passenger cars
and that more than 90 percent of them to the United States and
Canada. No breakdown by country was given.
   Hyundai Motor Co. topped the list with 33,803 autos, followed by
Kia Motors Corp. with 10,360 and Daewoo Motor with 5,716. No
year-earlier statistics were given.
   To the United States and Canada, Hyundai shipped 29,593 unts and
Daewoo 5,536. Kia said almost all of its February exports went to
the United States.
   The three Korean automakers' worldwide exports in the first two
months of this year totaled 95,687 cars, up 91.6 percent from the
same period last year.
   Hyundai's two month share was 69,636 cars, followed by Kia with
13,745 and Daewoo with 12,306.
   The three companies said they plan to export 685,000 cars this
year, up about 25 percent from last year.
</TEXT>
