<HEAD>London Shares Fall</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with market activity, closing
index; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices fell Monday on the London Stock
Exchange as the British pound rose in foreign-exchange markets,
making British exports more expensive.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
was down 16.3 points, or 0.88 percent, at 1818.2.
   A moderate 404.8 million shares were traded, down from 579.7
million on Friday which had been the most active session since Dec.
18.
   Dealers said banks and other financial stocks were among the
worst affected. Companies heavily involved in exports to
Continental Europe also lost ground.
